rominence in LA's Syrian cultural festivals, and in more recent activities of the grandchildren of immigrants to reclaim a sense of Arabness. Gualtieri reinscribes Syrians into Southern California history through her examination of powerful images and texts, augmented with interviews with descendants of immigrants. Telling the story of how Syrians helped forge a global Los Angeles, Arab Routes counters a long-held stereotype of Arabs as outsiders and underscores their longstanding place in American culture and in interethnic coalitions, past and present.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aArab AmericansxRelations with Hispanic AmericansxHistory. 0aArab AmericanszCalifornia, SouthernxEthnic identity. 0aImmigrantsxCultural assimilationzCalifornia, Southern. 0aSyrian AmericanszCalifornia, SouthernxEthnic identity. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh  aMexicanidad.  aSouthern California.  aSyrian-Americans.  aarchives.  ainter-ethnic solidarities.  amigration.  aoral history.  atransnationalism.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311069228040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150361086640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503610866423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503610866.jpg  a978-3-11-069228-0  SUP Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-